"{\"uid\": \"elliotlakestandard.ca-news-torch-run-and-barbeque-raise-9k-plus-for-special-olympics\", \"text\": \"On June 20, a total of 33 local Special Olympics athletes and volunteers along with police officers and supporters, for a total of 55, participated in the annual Law Enforcement Torch Run for Special Olympics in Elliot Lake.  TheOPP Torch Run started at ScotiaBank and ended at the OPP detachment in Elliot Lake.The Law Enforcement Torch Run is a fundraiser for Special Olympics across the province.  The local Law Enforcement Torch Run raised $7,365.  In addition, Foodland hosted a barbecue fundraiser for Special Olympics on June 15, which raised $2,095, says Julie Nykyforak, of Elliot Lake Special Olympics.  \\\"The Foodland barbeque was definitely a success. We would like to thank Foodland and their suppliers for hosting the barbeque,\\\" says Nykyforak. \\\"The support from this wonderful community was felt.\\\"  They are also grateful to the OPP for their continued support for Special Olympics. The two events combine raised a total of $9,460.  The funds raised are used to cover travel and other expenses for Special Olympics competitions. Throughout the year local athletes participate in: track and field, snowshoeing, swimming and bowling.  Postmedia is committed to maintaining a lively but civil forum for discussion. Please keep comments relevant and respectful. Comments may take up to an hour to appear on the site. You will receive an email if there is a reply to your comment, an update to a thread you follow or if a user you follow comments. Visit ourCommunity Guidelinesfor more information.  365 Bloor Street East, Toronto, Ontario, M4W 3L4  \\u00a9 2025 Elliot Lake Standard, a division of Postmedia Network Inc. All rights reserved. Unauthorized distribution, transmission or republication strictly prohibited.  This website uses cookies to personalize your content (including ads), and allows us to analyze our traffic. Read more aboutcookies here. By continuing to use our site, you agree to ourTerms of UseandPrivacy Policy.\"}"